{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_98","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented `FW-M7-004`.\n\nThe canonical edge artifact at `processed_coupling_dir/edges/<pre>__to__<post>_coupling.npz` is now a real assembled coupling bundle instead of a raw mapped-synapse dump. The new contract/config surface is in [coupling_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/coupling_contract.py#L42), the assembly logic is in [coupling_assembly.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/coupling_assembly.py#L25), and [synapse_mapping.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py#L240) now writes and loads edge bundles with component tables, source/target anchor clouds, blocked-synapse tables, and richer root-index metadata. Downstream code can now use `load_edge_coupling_bundle`, `lookup_edge_coupling_bundle`, `lookup_edge_coupling_components`, and `lookup_edge_blocked_synapses` from [synapse_mapping.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py#L500) instead of reconstructing coupling from raw rows.\n\nConfig plumbing now normalizes and records `meshing.coupling_assembly` in the build path and manifest snapshot via [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L67) and [geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py#L841). The bundle metadata now explicitly records topology family, kernel family, sign representation, delay model plus parameters, aggregation rule, and source/target cloud normalization. I also updated the example config and coupling design notes to document the shipped defaults.\n\nVerified with `make test` (`54` tests, all passing) and focused coupling runs including [tests/test_coupling_assembly.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_coupling_assembly.py#L25), which asserts deterministic bundle serialization plus sign handling, Euclidean delay assignment, blocked-row visibility, and multi-synapse aggregation semantics."}}
